  "text": "Dox cardiomyopathy was induced in 8-week-old male Wistar rats (Harlan) by intraperitoneal injection of Dox as previously described. [CITATION_1] A total dose of 15 mg/kg was administered over a 3-week period. In the first study, rats were divided to four groups. Group A (n ¼ 40) received subcutaneous Epo 20 U/kg, three times weekly, starting one week before initial Dox injection and continued for an additional week after final Dox administration. Group B (n ¼ 40) received 200 U/kg of Epo, employing a similar schedule. Control group (n ¼ 40; Group C) received PBS. Fourth group (n ¼ 10, group D) received subcutaneous Epo 20 U/ kg, three times weekly, similar to Group A with no subsequent Dox injections. The animals were allocated randomly to each of the study groups, after recording their weights. The number of animals was selected based on the estimated high mortality in this model and the need to complete the study with at least seven rats for the echocardiographic study (aiming to detect a meaningful change in FS).",
